>﻿</span>a<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>r<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>t<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>n<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>e<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>r<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>s</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span> </span></span></span></span></p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">&nbsp;The data-PASS documents are mor explicit than those of many archives.&nbsp; The&nbsp;rating is a 3 only because the intention of succession is documented, but there is no specific succession plan.&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p>',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(176,20,'A. Organizational Structure','A4. Financial Sustainability','<p>Fiscal and fiduciary policies, procedures, protocols, requirements; budgets and financial analysis documents; fiscal calendars; business plan(s); any evidence of active monitoring and preparedness.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://drupal.icpsr.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSR/node/1911\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A4.5</strong> Repository commits to monitoring for and bridging gaps in funding.</h3>','<p>ICPSR maintains a reserve to cover six months of operational expenses should there be a gap in funding and this reserve is well-documented in the budgetary documents produced three times per year for review by the ICPSR Council and in documents that support ICPSR\'s <em>Annual Report <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/publications/index.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/publications/index.jsp</a></em></p><p>The existing reserve should cover most gaps and allow ICPSR time to identify additional sources of funding.&nbsp;</p><p>[Digital Preservation, 23 March 2011]</p>',3,'Evidence Reviewed',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(229,2,'A. Organizational Structure','A1. Governance &amp; Organizational Viability','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">Mission statement for the repository; mission statement for the organizational context in which the repository sits; legal or legislative mandate; regulatory requirements.</span></p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><strong>A1.1</strong>&nbsp;Repository has a mission statement that reflects a commitment to the long-term retention of, management of, and access to digital information.</h3><p>&nbsp;</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><ul><li>\"ICPSR provides leadership and training in data access, curation, and methods of analysis for a diverse and expanding social science research community.\" (source: ICPSR Mission Statement;&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #027ac6; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/org/mission.html\" href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/org/mission.html\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/org/mission.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li><li>\"Strategic Direction 1: Leadership Role. Through global leadership and strong partnerships, set standards for excellence in data curation and in the ethics of data access and protection for the social sciences and related disciplines. Strategy A: Drive the development of next-generation tools and standards for data curation” the active management and enhancement of trusted digital resources across the life cycle.\" (source: ICPSR Strategic Plan;<a style=\"color: #027ac6; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction1.html\" href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction1.html\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction1.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>',4,'Evidence Reviewed',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(230,3,'A. Organizational Structure','A1. Governance &amp; Organizational Viability','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">Succession plan(s); escrow plan(s); explicit and specific statement documenting the intent to ensure continuity of the repository, and the steps taken and to be taken to ensure continuity; formal documents describing exit strategies and contingency plans; depositor agreements.</span></p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><strong>A1.2</strong>&nbsp;Repository has an appropriate, formal succession plan, contingency plans, and/or escrow arrangements in place in case the repository ceases to operate or the governing or funding institution substantially changes its scope.</h3><p>&nbsp;</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">Data-PASS partnership agreement: \"In the event that one of the partner institutions should no longer be able to retain the material they acquire, it will be transferred to one of the other partners. Both the original material and any additional material derived from the originals will be transferred.\" (Data-PASS Articles of Collaboration;<a style=\"color: #027ac6; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/DATAPASS/pdf/collaboration.pdf\" href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/DATAPASS/pdf/collaboration.pdf\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/DATAPASS/pdf/collaboration.pdf</a>) [Collection Development (Jared Lyle), 7/20/2009].&nbsp; The Data-PASS steering committee has drafted a more recent and comprehensive partnership agreement&nbsp;that is circulating for signature.&nbsp; &nbsp;[Digital Preservation, 23 March 2011]</span></p><p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">The Data-PASS partners are the most logical possible successors should ICPSR no longer be able to carry out its mission as a social science data archive.&nbsp; The Data-PASS policies, agreements, and expectations are well-documented : <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/DATAPASS/best-practices.jsp \"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/DATAPASS/best-practices.jsp</span></span></a>&nbsp;</span></p>',3,'Action Item(s)','<p>Enter the&nbsp;<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>link to the more recent Data-PAS<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span></span><span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span>S<span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span><span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span><span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span><span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span><span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span><span id=\"_mce_start\" style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\">﻿</span><span id=\"_m