 to be taken to ensure continuity; formal documents describing exit strategies and contingency plans; depositor agreements.</span></p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\"> </span></p><h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><strong>A1.2</strong> Repository has an appropriate, formal succession plan, contingency plans, and/or escrow arrangements in place in case the repository ceases to operate or the governing or funding institution substantially changes its scope.</h3><p>&nbsp;</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">Data-PASS partnership agreement: \"In the event that one of the partner institutions should no longer be able to retain the material they acquire, it will be transferred to one of the other partners. Both the original material and any additional material derived from the originals will be transferred.\" (Data-PASS Articles of Collaboration;<a title=\"https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/DATAPASS/pdf/collaboration.pdf\" href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/DATAPASS/pdf/collaboration.pdf\" style=\"color: #027ac6; text-decoration: none;\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/DATAPASS/pdf/collaboration.pdf</a>) [Collection Development (Jared Lyle), 7/20/2009].  The Data-PASS steering committee has drafted a more recent and comprehensive partnership agreement that is circulating for signature.   [Digital Preservation, 23 March 2011]</span></p><p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">The Data-PASS partners are the most logical possible successors should ICPSR no longer be able to carry out its mission as a social science data archive.  The Data-PASS policies, agreements, and expectations are well-documented : <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/DATAPASS/best-practices.jsp \"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/DATAPASS/best-practices.jsp</span></span></a> </span></p>',4,'Evidence Reviewed','<p><span style=\"line-height: 0; display: none;\" id=\"_mce_start\"> </span></p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\"> The data-PASS documents are more explicit than those of many archives and form the basis for implementing a succession plan if needed. </span></p><p>&nbsp;</p>',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(323,6,'A. Organizational Structure','A2. Organizational Structure &amp; Staffing','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">Professional development plans and reports; training requirements and training budgets, documentation of training expenditures (amount per staff); performance goals and documentation of staff assignments and achievements, copies of certificates awarded.</span></p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\"> </span></p><h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><strong>A2.3</strong> Repository has an active professional development program in place that provides staff with skills and expertise development opportunities.</h3><p>&nbsp;</p>','<ul><li><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">ICPSR Professional Development Policy (Source: <a href=\"https://drupal.icpsr.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSR/node/1600\" style=\"color: #027ac6; text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSR/node/1600</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</span></li><li><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">Documented in individual development plans [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</span></li></ul>',3,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\"> </span></p><ul><li>Training budget and expenditures (per staff)?</li><li>Performance goals and achievements?</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(324,1,'A. Organizational Structure','A2. Organizational Structure &amp; Staffing','<p>A staffing plan; competency definitions; job description; development plans; plus evidence that the repository review and maintains these documents as requirements evolve.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<p>A2.1 Repository has identified and established the duties that it needs to perform and has appointed staff with adequate skills and experience to fulfill these duties</p>','<p><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Symbol; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7pt/normal &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 7.5pt;\">\"The file attached here has our draft position descriptions for six job title: Research Technician - Senior...Research Area Specialist - Lead.\" (Source:https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSR/node/1387) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Symbol; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7pt/normal &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 7.5pt;\">\"Career Path Grid Collection Development\" Excel file (Source: <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSR/node/1596\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSR/node/1596</span></a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Symbol; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">·<span style=\"font: 7pt/normal &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 7.5pt;\">ICPSR has defined job descriptions and development paths for key life cycle positions: acquisitions, data processors and managers (responsible for Ingest and ongoing curation), digital curation (pending hire responsbile for life cycle coordination including preservation), collection delivery (access and dissemination) [digital preservation, May 2012]</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\"> </span></p>',4,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />','<html />',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(325,7,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<html />','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3>A3.1 Repository has defined its designated community(ies) and  associated knowledge base(s) and has publicly accessible definitions  and policies in place to dictate how its preservation service  requirements will be met.</h3>','<ul><li>\"...a diverse and expanding social science research community.\" (Source: ICPSR Mission Statement; <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/org/mission.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/org/mission.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><ul><li>\"Develop  a strong community that consists of ICPSR members and others in the  broader world of education, science, and public policy.\" (Source: ICPSR  Strategic Plan; <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction2.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction2.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><ul><li>\"You  will need basic statistical skills for using the online analysis system  and more advanced skills for running your own analysis, although SAS,  SPSS, and Stata setup files are provided with many ICPSR datasets.\"  (Source: Data Use Tutorial; <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/help/newuser.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/help/newuser.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><ul><li>Accessing Data web page (<a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/help/newuser.html#03\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/help/newuser.html#03</a>) [explaining service levels] [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><ul><li>Membership web page (<a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/membership/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/membership/index.html</a>) [explaining services for members] [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li><li>ICPSR Access Policy Framework (<a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/dpp-framework.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/access-policy-framework.jsp;jsessionid=DB53F7C2E40EFE90A5712CBEF5BFA0CE</a> )</li><li>ICPSR Digital Preservation Policy Framework (<a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/dpp-framework.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/dpp-framework.jsp</a> )</li></ul>',3,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />',NULL,1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,NULL),(326,8,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<p>Written documentation in the form of policies, procedures, protocols,  rules, manuals, handbooks, and workflows; specification of review cycle  for documentation; documentation detailing review, update, and  development mechanisms. If documentation is embedded in system logic,  functionality should demonstrate the implementation of policies and  procedures.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A3.2</strong> Repository has procedures and policies in place, and  mechanisms for their review, update, and development as the repository  grows and as technology and community practice evolve.</h3>','<ul><li>ICPSR Policies (Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/org/policies/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/org/policies/index.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><ul><li>Digital Preservation Policies (Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/</a>) [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li></ul><ul><li>ICPSR Intranet (Source: <a href=\"http://drupal.icpsr.umich.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">http://drupal.icpsr.umich.edu/</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><ul><li>Working With Data page (Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/INTRA/data.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/INTRA/data.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li><li>Other high-level life cycle policies in place, e.g., Access Policy (Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/access-policy-framework.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/preservation/policies/access-policy-framework.jsp</a>), Collection Development Policy (Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/policies/colldev.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/policies/colldev.jsp</a>) [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li><li>Digital curation and preservation standards awareness and compliance is well-documented (Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/index.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/curation/index.jsp</a>) [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li><li>Life cycle policies are being formalized and the process to develop and maintain policies has been formalized with a template for well-formed policies in place [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>',3,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />','<html />',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(327,9,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<p>Deposit agreements; records schedule; digital preservation policies; records legislation and policies; service agreements.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A3.3</strong> Repository maintains written policies that specify the  nature of any legal permissions required to preserve digital content  over time, and repository can demonstrate that these permissions have  been acquired when needed.</h3>','<ul><li>\"I give my permission for the Data Collection to be used by  ICPSR for the following purposes, without limitation...to store,  translate, copy or re-format the Data Collection in any way to ensure  its future preservation and accessibility.\" (ICPSR Data Deposit Form;  Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/access/deposit/data-deposit-form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/access/deposit/data-deposit-form.pdf</span></span></a>)  [JAL, 7/20/2009] [This evidence was given before the new web site was  launched. No PDF deposit form seems to be available online as of  3/9/2010. EAM 4/13/2010.]</li></ul><ul><li>General Archive deposit form: <span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">\"I give my permission for the Data Collection to be used by ICPSR for the following purposes, without limitation: [RMC]</span></span></li></ul><blockquote>To redisseminate copies of the Data Collection in a variety of media formats<br />To promote and advertise the Data Collection in any publicity (in any form) for ICPSR<br />To describe, catalog, validate and document the Data Collection<br />To store, translate, copy or re-format the Data Collection in any way to ensure its future preservation and accessibility<br />To incorporate metadata or documentation in the Data Collection into public access catalogues\"</blockquote><ul><li><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"> </span></span><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">DataPASS deposit form: \"<span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">I  give my permission to ICPSR for the Data Collection to be used by  Data-PASS, through its Partners, for the following purposes, without  limitation: [RMC]</span></span></span></span></li></ul><blockquote>To redisseminate copies of the Data Collection in a variety of distribution formats according the standard terms of use of ICPSR<br />To promote and advertise the Data Collection in any publicity (in any form) for Data-PASS and ICPSR<br />To describe, catalog, validate and document the Data Collection<br />To store, translate, copy or re-format the Data Collection in any way to ensure its future preservation and accessibility<br />To incorporate metadata (cataloging information) or documentation in the Data Collection into public access catalogues\"</blockquote><ul><li><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"> </span></span></span></span>DSDR: [no section on preservation appears on test of DSDR deposit form]</li><li>CCEERC: \" \"</li><li>Robert Wood Johnson Foundation: \" \"</li><li>MDRC: \" \"</li><li>NACDA: \" \"</li><li>NACJD-BJS: \" \"</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\">NACJD-NIJ: \"<span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">National Institute of Justice Deposit Agreement Terms . . . <span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">I  further understand that ICPSR on behalf of NIJ will describe, catalog,  validate, store, translate, copy, or reformat the Data Collection to  ensure its preservation, protection and accessibility. ICPSR will  incorporate metadata or documentation about the Data Collection into  public access catalogues, and enhance, transform and/or rearrange the  Data Collection, including the data and metadata, to the extent  supported by NIJ for the purposes of protecting respondent  confidentiality and improving usability. Finally, ICPSR, in conjunction  with NIJ will, determine the appropriate level of data protection and  access, disseminate the Data Collection in a variety of media formats,  and may promote and advertise the Data Collection in a variety of  venues.\"</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">NACJD-OJJDP: [no section on preservation appears on test of deposit form]</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">NAHDAP: \" \"</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">PRA: \" \"</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">SAMHDA: \" \"</span></span></span></span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em><br /></em></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>',3,'Action Item(s)','<p>1. CONTENT OF THE AGREEMENTS: \"<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #800000;\">Repository   maintains written policies that specify the nature of any legal   permissions required to preserve digital content over time</span>\"</p> <ul><li>ICPSR should have a general guiding principles document for standardizing legal permissions policy. [RMC]</li><li>Consider if all deposit forms should contain at least bare minimum language. [RMC]</li><li>An  audit/clean-up of the current situation with the  deposit forms (see  evidence above) is needed. Each one should contain  minimum legal  permissions. [RMC]</li></ul> <p>2. ACCESSIBLE LOCATION OF THE AGREEMENTS: \"<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #800000;\">repository can demonstrate that these permissions have been acquired when needed.</span>\"</p> <ul><li>Currently   there is no central, easily accessible place where the legal  agreements  are kept, and where once could easily view the signed  deposit forms and  the language of the permissions statement used.  Issues: [RMC]</li></ul> <p><strong><em><br /> </em></strong></p>','<p>1. CONTENT OF THE AGREEMENTS</p> <ul><li>What   minimum information do we need in order to modify/preserve over  time?   File names, title, terms of use, who deposited it? [RMC]</li><li>The   fact that Depositors can easily by-pass the agreement should be    considered. Electronic signature is not required, as depositors can    claim it\'s on file (where? provable?), or choose other reasons not to    sign. [RMC] </li><li>We provide a legal policy for selected archives. [RMC]</li></ul> <p>2. ACCESSIBLE LOCATION OF THE AGREEMENTS</p> <ul><li>There are both online and hard copy deposit forms. [RMC] </li><li>Does   each agreement have the exact legal language written out, or do  they   reference versions of legal language in another form (similar to  our   codebook link to terms of use)? [RMC]</li><li>For the paper forms, where are they kept? Iron Mountain, a drawer for each archive on site, etc.? [RMC]</li><li>Can    we say we comply on all current deposit forms? What about those in  the   past? Can ICPSR produce deposit agreements for all deposits over  time?   Can we even locate deposit agreements (did they exist?) for all    deposits? Are they in Iron Mountain? Did the preservation language    change over time, under different ICPSR administrations? [RMC]</li><li>Do    the 14 entities that have deposit forms also provide PDF copies of  the   deposit form for those depositors who don\'t want to use the  electronic   version? Is that PDF version as up-to-date and identical to  the   electronic version? [RMC]</li></ul>',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(328,9,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<p>Deposit agreements; records schedule; digital preservation policies; records legislation and policies; service agreements.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A3.3</strong> Repository maintains written policies that specify the  nature of any legal permissions required to preserve digital content  over time, and repository can demonstrate that these permissions have  been acquired when needed.</h3>','<ul><li>\"I give my permission for the Data Collection to be used by  ICPSR for the following purposes, without limitation...to store,  translate, copy or re-format the Data Collection in any way to ensure  its future preservation and accessibility.\" (ICPSR Data Deposit Form;  Source: <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/access/deposit/data-deposit-form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/access/deposit/data-deposit-form.pdf</span></span></a>)  [JAL, 7/20/2009] [This evidence was given before the new web site was  launched. No PDF deposit form seems to be available online as of  3/9/2010. EAM 4/13/2010.]</li></ul><ul><li>General Archive deposit form: <span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">\"I give my permission for the Data Collection to be used by ICPSR for the following purposes, without limitation: [RMC]</span></span></li></ul><blockquote>To redisseminate copies of the Data Collection in a variety of media formats<br />To promote and advertise the Data Collection in any publicity (in any form) for ICPSR<br />To describe, catalog, validate and document the Data Collection<br />To store, translate, copy or re-format the Data Collection in any way to ensure its future preservation and accessibility<br />To incorporate metadata or documentation in the Data Collection into public access catalogues\"</blockquote><ul><li><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"> </span></span><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">DataPASS deposit form: \"<span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">I  give my permission to ICPSR for the Data Collection to be used by  Data-PASS, through its Partners, for the following purposes, without  limitation: [RMC]</span></span></span></span></li></ul><blockquote>To redisseminate copies of the Data Collection in a variety of distribution formats according the standard terms of use of ICPSR<br />To promote and advertise the Data Collection in any publicity (in any form) for Data-PASS and ICPSR<br />To describe, catalog, validate and document the Data Collection<br />To store, translate, copy or re-format the Data Collection in any way to ensure its future preservation and accessibility<br />To incorporate metadata (cataloging information) or documentation in the Data Collection into public access catalogues\"</blockquote><ul><li><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-ser