ppropriate level of data protection and  access, disseminate the Data Collection in a variety of media formats,  and may promote and advertise the Data Collection in a variety of  venues.\"</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">NACJD-OJJDP: [no section on preservation appears on test of deposit form]</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">NAHDAP: \" \"</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">PRA: \" \"</span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 3px;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium \'Times New Roman\'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\',Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: left;\">SAMHDA: \" \"</span></span></span></span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em><br /></em></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>',3,'Evidence Reviewed','<p>1. CONTENT OF THE AGREEMENTS: \"<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #800000;\">Repository   maintains written policies that specify the nature of any legal   permissions required to preserve digital content over time</span>\"</p> <ul><li>ICPSR should have a general guiding principles document for standardizing legal permissions policy. [RMC]</li><li>Consider if all deposit forms should contain at least bare minimum language. [RMC]</li><li>An  audit/clean-up of the current situation with the  deposit forms (see  evidence above) is needed. Each one should contain  minimum legal  permissions. [RMC]</li></ul> <p>2. ACCESSIBLE LOCATION OF THE AGREEMENTS: \"<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #800000;\">repository can demonstrate that these permissions have been acquired when needed.</span>\"</p> <ul><li>Currently   there is no central, easily accessible place where the legal  agreements  are kept, and where once could easily view the signed  deposit forms and  the language of the permissions statement used.  Issues: [RMC]</li></ul> <p><strong><em><br /> </em></strong></p>','<p>1. CONTENT OF THE AGREEMENTS</p> <ul><li>What   minimum information do we need in order to modify/preserve over  time?   File names, title, terms of use, who deposited it? [RMC]</li><li>The   fact that Depositors can easily by-pass the agreement should be    considered. Electronic signature is not required, as depositors can    claim it\'s on file (where? provable?), or choose other reasons not to    sign. [RMC] </li><li>We provide a legal policy for selected archives. [RMC]</li></ul> <p>2. ACCESSIBLE LOCATION OF THE AGREEMENTS</p> <ul><li>There are both online and hard copy deposit forms. [RMC] </li><li>Does   each agreement have the exact legal language written out, or do  they   reference versions of legal language in another form (similar to  our   codebook link to terms of use)? [RMC]</li><li>For the paper forms, where are they kept? Iron Mountain, a drawer for each archive on site, etc.? [RMC]</li><li>Can    we say we comply on all current deposit forms? What about those in  the   past? Can ICPSR produce deposit agreements for all deposits over  time?   Can we even locate deposit agreements (did they exist?) for all    deposits? Are they in Iron Mountain? Did the preservation language    change over time, under different ICPSR administrations? [RMC]</li><li>Do    the 14 entities that have deposit forms also provide PDF copies of  the   deposit form for those depositors who don\'t want to use the  electronic   version? Is that PDF version as up-to-date and identical to  the   electronic version? [RMC]</li></ul>',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(329,10,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<p>A self-assessment schedule, timetables for review and  certification; results of self-assessment; evidence of implementation of  review outcomes.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A3.4</strong> Repository is committed to formal, periodic review and  assessment to ensure responsiveness to technological developments and  evolving requirements.</h3>','<ul><li>\"ICPSR is committed to a two-year cycle of self-assessment and a  five-year audit cycle to evaluate, measure, and adjust the policies,  procedures, preservation approaches, and practices of the digital  preservation function.\" (Source: ICPSR Digital Preservation Policy  Framework; <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/DP/policies/dpp-framework.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/DP/policies/dpp-framework.html</a>) </li><li>ICPSR has established an audit and control function monitored by a registrar to track deposits [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li><li>ICPSR participated in one of the first test TRAC audits in 2006, established a formal self-assesment process, and commits to ongoing self-assessment [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li><li>ICPSR is a partner with other Data-PASS members in the SafeArchive.org, a LOCKSS-based application to demonstrate TRAC compliance through the definition and application of rules [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li><li>ICPSR is exploring the possibility of a peer review audit with Data-PASS members [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li></ul>',4,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />','<ul><li>Evidence of regular or periodic review? </li></ul>',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(330,11,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<p>A policy that requires a feedback mechanism; a procedure that addresses  how the repository seeks, captures, and documents responses to feedback;  documentation of workflow for feedback (i.e., how feedback is used and  managed); quality assurance records.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A3.5</strong> Repository has policies and procedures to ensure that feedback from producers and users is sought and addressed over time.</h3>','<ul><li>\"Implement a system to continuously monitor users\' and members\'  data needs, current use of/interaction with ICPSR resources, and needs  and desires for future use/interaction\" (ICPSR Strategic Plan, Direction  2: Membership Value, Strategy B, Objective 1; <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction2.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction2.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li></ul><ul><li>\"Schedule  periodic gatherings of various customer segments for the purpose of  exploring evolving needs, identifying challenges to use of ICPSR  resources, and generating new ideas for use.\" (ICPSR Strategic Plan,  Direction 2: Membership Value, Strategy B, Objective 3; <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction2.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/ICPSR/strategic/directions/direction2.html</a>) [JAL, 7/20/2009]</li><li>The  Web site has a feedback form that appears at the base of each page that  enables users to submit feedback regarding site errors/content issues. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/report-problem.jsp?url=http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/index.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/report-problem.jsp?url=http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/index.jsp</a> [MR, 2/16/2010]</li><li>The error pages and the \'no search results found\' pages include email address for Web support and User support. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/studies?archive=ICPSR&amp;q=genome+data\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/studies?archive=ICPSR&amp;q=genome+data</a>[MR, 2/16/2010]</li><li>The  Web site provides contact information on its Web site, as well as  detailed staff information, including email addresses and phone numbers.  <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/contact.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/contact.jsp</a>[MR, 2/16/2010]</li><li>ICPSR  maintains a ticketing system so that feedback sent to  web-support@icps.umich.edu or netmail@icpsr.umich.edu is logged and  reviewed. Feedback that arrives outside those channels is routinely  added into the ticketing system so that it can be tracked. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/shared/ICPSR/help/index\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/shared/ICPSR/help/index</a> [MR, 2/16/2010]</li><li>Every  two years, the Web team initiates the re-design process by soliciting  feedback from ICPSR staff, managers, and site users, via email to all  staff, OR-Announce, ICPSR-Announce, and posts on the Web site. That  feedback is reviewed and prioritized to determine how we will improve  the Web site as part of the re-design. <a href=\"http://icpsr.blogspot.com/2009_08_01_archive.html\">http://icpsr.blogspot.com/2009_08_01_archive.html</a>[MR, 2/16/2010]</li><li>When  preparing a re-design for the topical archives, the Web team meets with  the archive manager to determine what should be included with the  re-design. Unlike ICPSR, it is the responsibility of the archive manager  to solicit feedback from the funding agency. [MR, 2/16/2010]</li><li>Staff  suggestions are logged either in JIRA (for small tasks) or in the  Project Tracking System (for larger projects) where they are  evaluated/prioritized by the appropriate committees. [MR, 2/16/2010]</li><li>The  Web team is in the process of building a system whereby every site  manager meets with a Web developer once every six months to discuss  broadly how well the site is performing its task and how it might be  improved. This system should be in place for FY2010-2011. [MR,  2/16/2010]</li><li>Periodic surveys of the members solicit suggestions for new data and feedback on ICPSR resources and services. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/ICPSR/or/2010ORResearchReport.pptx\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/ICPSR/or/2010ORResearchReport.pptx</a>[Dissemination Committee]</li><li>Biennial meetings of the members solicit suggestions for new data and feedback on ICPSR resources and services. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/or/ormeet/index.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/or/ormeet/index.jsp</a>[Dissemination Committee]</li><li>ICPSR and its topical archives attend conferences where attendees get feedback on ICPSR resources and services. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/publications/index.jsp;jsessionid=B05716313CB3045FDFB13545B9AD82FB\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/publications/index.jsp;jsessionid=B05716313CB3045FDFB13545B9AD82FB</a>[Dissemination Committee]</li><li>ICPSR  staff are in contact with data producers before Ingest and throughout  the Ingest process until data are released. During this time feedback  can be elicited. [Dissemination Committee]</li><li>Council meets with  staff three times a year to provide guidance and feedback. Action items  are recorded and acted upon, usually by the time of the next Council  meeting. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/governance/index.jsp\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/org/governance/index.jsp</a>[Dissemination Committee]</li><li>ICPSR has a form on the Web site for users to suggest new data to archive. <a href=\"http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/access/deposit/suggest.jsp?source=deposit\">http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/ICPSR/access/deposit/suggest.jsp?source=deposit</a> [Dissemination Committee]</li><li>ICPSR  reviews and monitors a database of grants awarded by major funders  (NSF, NIH) to understand trends in research and to identify data that  should be archived. [Dissemination Committee]</li></ul>',4,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />','<ul><li>Outcomes from Marketing on contacting users (e.g., survey results, reports)? </li><li>Is a survey of data depositors and the deposit experience needed?</li></ul>',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(331,12,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<p>Policies, procedures, and results of changes that affect all levels of  the repository: objects, aggregations of objects; object-level  preservation metadata; repository\'s records retention strategy document.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A3.6</strong> Repository has a documented history of the changes to  its operations, procedures, software, and hardware that, where  appropriate, is linked to relevant preservation strategies and describes  potential effects on preserving digital content.</h3>',NULL,3,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />',NULL,1,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,1,NULL),(332,12,'A. Organizational Structure','A3. Procedural Accountability &amp; Policy Framework','<p>Policies, procedures, and results of changes that affect all levels of  the repository: objects, aggregations of objects; object-level  preservation metadata; repository\'s records retention strategy document.</p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<h3><strong>A3.6</strong> Repository has a documented history of the changes to  its operations, procedures, software, and hardware that, where  appropriate, is linked to relevant preservation strategies and describes  potential effects on preserving digital content.</h3>','<ul><li>ICPSR documents changes that affect life cycle management and can trace those changes explicitly over the past decade and generally for its fifty-year existence [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li></ul><ul><li>Acquisition decisions, deposit forms, deposit tracking and extent of processing, archival storage management decisions and actions, and dissemination actions are tracked [Digital Preservation, May 2012]</li></ul>',3,'Evidence Reviewed','<html />','<html />',1,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,NULL,1,1),(333,2,'A. Organizational Structure','A1. Governance &amp; Organizational Viability','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">Mission statement for the repository; mission statement for the organizational context in which the repository sits; legal or legislative mandate; regulatory requirements.</span></p>','<p>See <a href=\"https://webservices.itcs.umich.edu/drupal/ICPSRTRAC/node/86\">ICPSR Responsibilities for TRAC</a> for an explanation and details.</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><strong>A1.1</strong>&nbsp;Repository has a mission statement that reflects a commitment to the long-term retention of, management of, and access to digital information.</h3><p>&nbsp;</p>','<p><span style=\"color: #494949; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><ul><li>\"ICPSR provides leadership and training in data access, curation, and methods of analysis for a diverse and expanding social science research community.\" (source: ICPSR Mission Statement;&nbsp;<a style=\"col