INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','page',0,3,3,'und',0,'<h2>Roles and Responsibilities</h2><p>This page defines roles and responsibilties for a TDR Self-assessment and Audit project and outlines some suggestions for providing evidence for assigned ISO 16363 (TRAC) requirements. Each group is responsible for documenting the current&nbsp;level of compliance with a designated set of requirements.</p><h2>Stakeholder Groups</h2><p>The list below consists of the stakeholder groups that have a role to play in TRAC compliance. The name of each entity is linked to a page where TRAC roles and responsibilities are enumerated.</p><ul><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/senior-management\">Senior Management</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/coordination-group\">Coordination Group</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/operations-group\">Operations Group</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/information-technology\">Information Technology</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/administration-finance-or-hr\">Administration: Finance or HR</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/acquisitions\">Acquisitions</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/preservation\">Preservation</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/dissemination\">Dissemination</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/rights-management\">Rights Management</a></li><li><a href=\"/trac/stakeholders/external-advisory-group\">External Advisory Group</a></li></ul><h2><a title=\"raci\" name=\"raci\"></a>Responsibilities</h2><p>Stakeholder groups are assigned responsibilities using toles defined by the RASCI approach to project management. The RASCI Matrix describes participation by various organizational roles in completing tasks for a project. RACI is especially useful in clarifying roles in projects and processes requiring distributed responsibilities and adapts well to a TDR self-assessment and audit project.</p><p><em>Definitions of the RACI Categories:</em></p><ul><li><strong>Responsible:</strong> person or group who performs an activity or does the work</li><li><strong>Accountable:</strong> person or group who is ultimately accountable and has Yes/No/Veto</li><li><strong>Support:</strong> person or group that assists in completing task</li><li><strong>Consulted:</strong> person or group that needs to provide feedback and contribute to the activity</li><li><strong>Informed:</strong> person or group that needs to know of the decision or action</li></ul><p><strong><em>Note for clarification</em></strong>: Resources are allocated to <em>Responsible</em> who gets input from <em>Consulted,</em> assistance from <em>Support,</em> and guidance from <em>Accountable</em>. For more about RACI, see the following resources:</p><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.valuebasedmanagement.net/methods_raci.html\">RACI model | RACI chart | RACI method</a></li><li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsibility_assignment_matrix\">Wikipedia, Responsibility Assignment Matrix</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.zimbio.com/Project+Management+and+Technology/articles/17/Accountability+Great+Info+RASCI+RACI+Matrix\">Accountability: Great Info On The RASCI / RACI Matrix</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.projectsmart.co.uk/how-to-do-raci-charting-and-analysis.html\">How to Do RACI Charting and Analysis</a></li></ul><h2>Responsible</h2><p>For these requirements, the lead group will identify and/or develop examples of evidence to demonstrate the ways in which the repository complies with the requirement (see below for documentation examples).</p><ul><li>First, review each of the ISO 16363 requirements for which your group is responsible</li><li>Make quick progress by determining which requirements are already in place and are either already documented or might be easy to document</li><li>Next, determine the requirements that will require review or contributions by one or more members of the group; these sub-groups will bring recommendations back to the group</li><li>For each requirement, the responsible group will:<ul><li>determine the kinds of assistance needed from groups with a supporting role</li><li>seek feedback at appropriate points (e.g., when drafts are prepared, about specific topics) from groups with a consulting role</li><li>provide updates and report on outcomes to groups with an accountable role or an informed role (groups that should be aware of the results)</li></ul></li><li>Document how the repository has addressed or will address the requirement</li></ul><h2>Accountable</h2><p>For these requirements, the accountable group will actively track progress on documenting compliance.</p><ul><li>Maintain contact with the lead group until the requirement review is completed, compliance is documented, and relevant next steps are determined, when applicable</li><li>Ensure that the responsible group documents their progress on Drupal</li></ul><h2>Support</h2><p>For these requirements, the Support group should offer assistance to the lead group.</p><ul><li>Contact the responsible group to coordinate efforts</li><li>Contribute to the documentation for these requirements upon request by the lead group</li></ul><h2>Consulted</h2><p>For these requirements, the Consulted group should coordinate with the lead group to determine when and how to provide feedback</p><ul><li>Contact the responsible group to determine your group\'s role in the process</li><li>Determine how your group\'s expertise or position within the organization can best assist the responsible group</li></ul><h2>Informed</h2><p>For these requirements, the Informed group will track progress by lead group to ensure awareness of the status.</p><ul><li>Though the informed role sounds passive, it involves active awareness of the process and results.</li><li>Contact the responsible group to learn about the planned approach for these requirements.</li></ul><h3>Compiling and Generating Documentation to Address Requirements</h3><p>For each requirement, the Responsible role leads on compiling and/or generating relevant evidence. When evidence already exists, the responsible group will document the evidence of compliance, e.g., by linking to an existing online policy or procedure, or posting the policy or procedures either for internal or public access.&nbsp;&nbsp;A more narrative form for capturing evidence, such as blog posts or other written descriptions of&nbsp;relevant efforts, may be effective,&nbsp;especially when the action or outcome required by TRAC is already in place, but these actions (procedures and practices) have not yet been documented.&nbsp;The TDR Self-asessment and Audit (aka TRAC Review) pages provide a framework for capturing documentation and documenting the status of TDR compliance, so each group should adapt the requirements pages for their own use. Please add suggestions to this page as you complete your own requirements.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','page',0,4,4,'und',0,'<p>This page provides an overview of an organization\'s efforts&nbsp;to document its evidence for meeting the requirements of the CCSDS Audit and Certification of Trustworthy Digital Repositories <a title=\"checklist\" href=\"http://public.ccsds.org/publications/archive/652x0m1.pdf\">checklist</a>&nbsp;that was a pproved as ISO 16363 and is based on Trustworthy Repositories Audit and Certification (TRAC): Criteria and Checklist that was released in January 2007. These webpages support a self-assessment and audit (aka TRAC Review) method for an organization to demonstrate&nbsp;good practice and conformance&nbsp;as a trusted digital repository (TDR) to its designated communities and prepare for a peer review or other external audit. In many organizations, responsibilities for TDR compliance are distributed throughout the organization, with specific units and committees having certain responsibilities for each requirement.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities<br /></strong>Each entity is assigned a role for each requirement using the RACI responsibility assignment matrix. The RACI Matrix describes participation by various organizational roles in completing tasks for a project. RACI is especially useful in clarifying roles in projects and processes requiring distributed responsibilities. See the <a href=\"/trac/node/3\">Responsibilities</a>&nbsp;for TDR Self-assessment and Audit page for more information on RACI responsibilities, and a listing of units and committees that have roles in TRAC conformance.</p><p><strong>Requirements<br /></strong>Each TDR requirement&nbsp;has its own page. Sub- and Sub-sub requirements are referred to on the relevant high-level requirement page. Current compliance with TDR requirements is assessed on a rating system from 0 to 4 (see example: <a href=\"/trac/sites/default/files/SGDS%202009-9421%20%28D.%20BOUCON%29.pdf\">SGDS report</a>, page 14):<br />&nbsp; <strong>4</strong> = fully compliant - the repository can demonstrate that has comprehensively addressed the requirement<br />&nbsp; <strong>3</strong> = mostly compliant - the repository&nbsp;can demonstrate that it&nbsp;has mostly addressed the requirement and&nbsp;is&nbsp;on working on full compliance<br />&nbsp; <strong>2</strong> = half compliant - the repository has partially addressed the requirement and has&nbsp;significant work&nbsp;remaining to fully address the requirement<br />&nbsp; <strong>1</strong> = slightly compliant - the repositroy has something in place, but has a&nbsp;lot of work to do in addressing the requirement&nbsp;<br />&nbsp; <strong>0</strong> = non-compliant or not started - the repository has not yet addressed the requirement or has not started the review of the requirement<br />Any group&nbsp;in the organization&nbsp;that is involved in defining policy and practice should update the status of relevant requirements. When listing evidence, please include sufficient information for reviewers to get to the cited evidence (e.g., a document title, date, a link) and note the name of the group or department that is adding an entry to the evidence addressing the requirement along with the date of the annotations (e.g., [Right Management group, 2/13/2013]). For additional guidance, please see the&nbsp;<a href=\"/trac/node/3\">Responsibilities</a>&nbsp;for TDR Self-assessment and Audit page.</p><p><strong>Status<br /></strong>The summary below reflects this sequence of status levels.<strong><br /></strong>&nbsp; <strong>A</strong>ccepted&nbsp;– the evidence provided has been accepted as sufficient for this review round<br />&nbsp; <strong>R</strong>eady for review – the Responsible group has completed its work and the evidence is ready for review<br />&nbsp; <strong>I</strong>n progress – the Responsible group is in the process of compiling or generating relevant evidence<br />&nbsp; <strong>N</strong>ot started – no evidence or information has been provided yet</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,7,499,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure commitment to preservation, retention, management and access at the repository’s highest administrative level.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,432,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to help the repository make administrative decisions, shape policies, and allocate resources in order to successfully preserve its holdings.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,9,360,'und',0,'This is necessary in order that the repository has guidance on acquisition of digital content it will preserve, retain, manage and provide access to.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,13,219,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository has the rights and authorizations needed to enable it to collect and preserve digital content over time, make that information available to its Designated Community, and defend those rights when challenged.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,14,275,'und',0,'This is necessary in order that there is a clear understanding of what needs to be acquired\r\nfrom the Producer.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,15,367,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order that it is possible to test that the repository meets the needs of its Designated Community.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,16,368,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository can fulfill that part of its mission related to preservation.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,17,321,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to provide an ‘audit trail’ through which stakeholders can identify\r\nand trace decisions made by the repository.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,18,77,'und',0,'This is necessary because transparency, in the sense of being available to anyone who wishes\r\nto know, is the best assurance that the repository operates in accordance with accepted\r\nstandards and practices.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,19,502,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to provide documentation that it has developed or adapted appropriate measures for ensuring the integrity of its holding.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,20,79,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure the repository continues to be trustworthy and there is no\r\nthreat to its content.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,21,80,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure the viability of the repository over the period of time it\r\nhas promised to provide access to its contents for its Designated Community.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,22,81,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to guard against malfeasance or other untoward activity that might\r\nthreaten the economic viability of the repository.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,23,262,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to demonstrate that the repository has identified and documented\r\nthese categories, and actively manages them, including identifying and responding to risks,\r\ndescribing and leveraging benefits, specifying and balancing investments, and anticipating\r\nand preparing for expenditures.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,24,84,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to allow the repository to track, act on, and verify rights and\r\nrestrictions related to the use of the digital objects within the repository.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,25,276,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to make it clear to funders, depositors, and users what\r\nresponsibilities the repository is taking on and what aspects are excluded. It is also a\r\nnecessary step in defining the information which is needed from the information producers or\r\ndepositors.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,26,504,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to be sure that the repository is able to extract information from the SIPs.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,27,500,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to avoid providing erroneous provenance to the information which is preserved.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,28,505,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to detect and correct errors in the SIP when created and potential transmission errors between the depositor and the repository.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,29,501,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the preservation can be accomplished, with physical control, and is authorized, with legal control.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,30,506,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the producer can verify that there are no inadvertent lapses in communication which might otherwise allow loss of SIPs.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,31,264,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure that such documentation, which may be needed in an audit, is\r\ncaptured and is accurate and authentic.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,32,510,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary to ensure that the AIP and its associated definition, including appropriate Packaging Information, can always be found, processed and managed within the archive.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,33,513,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the AIP(s) adequately represents the information in the SIP(s).</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,34,530,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the SIPs received have been dealt with appropriately, and in particular have not been accidentally lost.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,36,384,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository’s digital objects are understandable to the Designated Community.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,37,545,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that an auditable trail to support claims of authenticity is available, that unauthorized changes to the digital holdings can be detected, and that the digital objects can be identified and placed in their appropriate context.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,38,393,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that one of the primary tests of preservation, namely that the digital holdings are understandable by their Designated Community, can be met. (See 4.3 for additional requirements for understandability beyond ingest.)</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,39,532,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that what is maintained over the long term is as it should be and can be traced to the information provided by the Producers.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,40,507,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary to enable the audit of the integrity of the collection as a whole.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,41,531,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that there is omitted from the record nothing relevant that might be needed to provide an independent means to verify that all AIPs have been properly created in accord with the documented procedures (see 4.2.1 through 4.2.9). It is the responsibility of the repository to justify its practice in this respect.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,42,524,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order that it is clear how the repository plans to ensure the information will remain available and usable for future generations and to provide a means to check and validate the preservation work of the repository.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,43,525,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary so that the repository can react to changes and thereby ensure that the preserved information remains understandable and usable by the Designated Community.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,44,527,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order for the repository to be prepared for changes in the external environment that may make its current preservation plans a bad choice as the time to implement draws near.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,45,498,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to assure the Designated Community that the repository will be able to make the information available and usable over the mid-to-long-term.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,46,518,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the information can be extracted from the AIP over the long-term.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,47,520,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure documentation is not omitted or erroneous or of questionable authenticity.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,48,515,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to enable discovery of the repository’s holdings.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,49,516,'und',0,'<p>This is required in order to ensure that descriptive information is associated with the AIP.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,50,517,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary to ensure that all AIPs can be located and retrieved.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,51,251,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure the repository has fully addressed all aspects of usage\r\nwhich might affect the trustworthiness of the repository, particularly with reference to\r\nsupport of the user community.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,52,514,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary to establish an auditable chain of authenticity from the AIP to disseminated digital objects.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,53,231,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure a secure and trustworthy infrastructure.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,54,233,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to assert that the repository is providing an authentic copy of a\r\nparticular digital object.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,55,369,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary to ensure ongoing and uninterrupted service to the Designated Community.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,56,224,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that controls are in place to meet the security needs of the\r\nrepository.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,57,225,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that individuals have the authority to implement changes,\r\nthat adequate resources have been assigned for the effort, and that the responsible individuals\r\nwill be accountable for implementing such changes.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,58,226,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that sufficient backup and recovery capabilities are in\r\nplace to facilitate continuing preservation of and access to systems and their content with\r\nlimited disruption of services.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,61,435,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository can recognize when it is necessary to execute those plans.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,62,216,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository can complete all tasks associated with\r\nthe long-term preservation and management of the data objects.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,63,322,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure repository staffing levels are adequate for preserving the\r\ndigital content and providing a secure, quality repository.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,64,217,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure that staff skill sets evolve as the repository technology and\r\npreservation procedures change.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,65,218,'und',0,'This is necessary in order that the repository has up-to-date, complete policies and\r\nprocedures in place that reflect the current requirements and practices of its community(ies)\r\nfor preservation.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,66,272,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to have sufficient control of the information for preservation and\r\nlimit the repository’s exposure to liability or legal and financial harm.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,67,220,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the respective roles of repository, producers, and\r\ncontributors in the depositing of digital content and transfer of responsibility for preservation\r\nare understood and accepted by all parties.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,68,336,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to avoid misunderstandings between the repository and\r\nproducer/depositor as to when and how the transfer of responsibility for the digital content\r\noccurs.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,69,274,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to minimize potential liability and challenges to the rights of the\r\nrepository.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,70,269,'und',0,'This is necessary to establish a clear understanding with depositors, funders, and the\r\nrepository’s Designated Communities how the repository determines and checks what the\r\ncharacteristics and properties of preserved items will be over the long term. These procedures\r\nwill be necessary to confirm authenticity or to identify erroneous claims of authenticity of the\r\npreserved digital record.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,71,511,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary to ensure that the appropriate definition is used when parsing/interpreting an AIP.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,72,512,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to explicitly show that the AIPs are fit for their intended purpose, that each component of an AIP has been adequately conceived and executed and the plans for the maintenance of each AIP are in place. (See 4.3, Preservation Planning, below.)</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,74,536,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that each AIP can be unambiguously found in the future. This is also necessary to ensure that each AIP can be distinguished from all other AIPs in the repository.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,80,540,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order that actions relating to AIPs can be traced over time, over system changes, and over storage changes.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,91,526,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the preserved information remains understandable and usable by the Designated Community.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,92,529,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that the preserved information remains understandable and usable by the Designated Community.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,93,519,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary because it is the fundamental mission of a repository to preserve the Content Information for its Designated Communities.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,94,280,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to protect the integrity of the archival objects over time.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,95,523,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that any actions performed against an AIP do not alter the AIP information in a manner unacceptable to its Designated Communities.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,96,522,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure that any actions performed against an AIP do not alter the AIP information in a manner unacceptable to its Designated Communities.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,97,261,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure that all AIPs can continue to be located and retrieved.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,98,255,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to identify security threats and access management system failures.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,99,509,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order for the users to consider the repository to be a trustworthy source of information.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,100,229,'und',0,'This is necessary to track when hardware or software components will become obsolete and\r\nmigration is needed to new infrastructure.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,101,235,'und',0,'This is necessary to provide expected, contracted, secure, and persistent levels of service\r\nincluding: ease of ingest and dissemination through appropriate depositor and user interfaces\r\nand technologies such as upload mechanisms; on-going digital object management;\r\npreservation approaches and solutions, such as migration; and system security.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,102,232,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure expected, contracted, secure, and persistent levels of service.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,103,234,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure that the repository has the capacity to make informed and timely\r\ndecisions when information indicates the need for new hardware.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,104,236,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure hardware replacement in a timely fashion so as to avert system\r\nfailure or performance inadequacy. Without such a commitment, and more importantly,\r\nwithout escrowed financial resources or a secure funding stream, technology watches and\r\nnotifications are of little value. The repository must have mechanisms for evaluating the\r\nefficacy of the new systems before implementation in the production system.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,105,237,'und',0,'This is necessary to provide expected, contracted, secure, and persistent levels of service\r\nincluding: ease of ingest and dissemination through appropriate depositor and user interfaces\r\nand technologies such as upload mechanisms; on-going digital object management;\r\npreservation approaches and solutions, such as migration; and system security.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,106,330,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure expected, contracted, secure, and persistent levels of service.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,107,239,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure that the repository has the capacity to make informed and timely\r\ndecisions when information indicates the need for new software.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,108,240,'und',0,'This is necessary to ensure software replacement in a timely fashion so as to avert system\r\nfailure or performance inadequacy. Without such a commitment, and more importantly,\r\nwithout escrowed financial resources or a secure funding stream, technology watches and\r\nnotifications are of little value. The repository must have mechanisms for evaluating the\r\nefficacy of the new systems before implementation in the production system.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,109,503,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to ensure continued access to and tracking of preservation functions applied to the digital objects in their custody.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,110,242,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that AIPs and metadata are uncorrupted or any data\r\nlosses are detected and fall within the tolerances established by repository policy (see 3.3.5).','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,111,243,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure the repository administration is being kept informed of\r\nincidents and recovery actions, and to enable identification of sources of data corruption or\r\nloss.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,112,244,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to protect the integrity of the archival objects from unauthorized\r\nchanges or deletions.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,113,246,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that data is not lost when either the media fail or the\r\nsupporting hardware can no longer be used to access the data.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,114,247,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the critical processes can be monitored to ensure that\r\nthey continue to meet the mandatory responsibilities and to ensure that any changes to those\r\nprocesses are examined and tested.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,115,248,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository can specify not only the current\r\nprocesses, but the prior processes that were applied to the repository holdings.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,116,249,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to protect the integrity of the repository’s critical processes such\r\nthat they continue in their ability to meet the repository’s mandatory requirements.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,117,250,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that multiple copies of a digital object remain identical,\r\nwithin a time established as acceptable by the repository, and that a copy can be used to\r\nreplace a corrupted copy of the object.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,119,434,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to preserve the information content entrusted to the repository by handing it on to another custodian in the case that the repository ceases to operate.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,120,331,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to identify in writing the Content Information of the records for\r\nwhich it has taken preservation responsibility and the Information Properties it has\r\ncommitted to preserve for those records based on their Content Information.','',NULL),('node','page',0,121,429,'und',0,'<h2>Purpose and Scope</h2><p>This site is designed to assist any organization with responsibility for the long-term management of digital content to completing a TRAC Review as a means to demonstrate its alignment with prevailing digital curation and preservation standards and good practice.</p><p>The site supports both self-assessment and preparation for an external audit. There is an auditor role with a separate log-in that can see all of the content on the site and has exclusive editing rights to an audit comment field.&nbsp; Organization’s can incorporate the auditor role into their TRAC review process. One possible approach might be to freeze the content and effectively turning the site over to one or more auditors for a period of time then reviewing the results. The TRAC Review site is intentionally not prescriptive about how the site is used so any organization can use it.</p><h2>TRAC Requirements</h2><p>This TRAC Review site reflects the requirements as defined in the CCSDS Audit and Certification of Trustworthy Digital Repositories <a title=\"checklist\" href=\"http://public.ccsds.org/publications/archive/652x0m1.pdf\">checklist</a> that was approved as ISO 16363 in 2012. &nbsp;ISO 16363 is based on the Trustworthy Repository Audit and Certification (<a href=\"http://www.crl.edu/sites/default/files/attachments/pages/trac_0.pdf\">TRAC</a>): Criteria and Checklist that was developed by the RLG/NARA Task Force beginning in 2003 and released for public use in January 2007. The requirements pages reflect the 2012 version of the requirements with a link to the relevant 2007 version of the requirement. All of the information from the CCSDS document is included in this TRAC review site.</p><h2>Process</h2><p>This site incorporates an optional approach to roles and responsibilities that adopts the <a href=\"http://www.valuebasedmanagement.net/methods_raci.html\">RA(S)CI</a> project management roles as described on the Responsibilities page (see links for information about those aspects).&nbsp; The process envisioned in using this TRAC Review site includes completing the following steps for each requirement (noting optional steps):</p><ul><li><strong><em>Identify <a href=\"/trac/responsibilities\">roles</a></em></strong>: e.g., senior management, preservation, rights management&nbsp; (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Assign <a href=\"/trac/responsibilities\">responsibilities</a></em></strong>: e.g., responsible, accountable, support, consulted, informed (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Enter evidence</em></strong>: note who provided what evidence when using the examples from the CCSDS document as a guide to provide a cumulative record and to show progress (Required)</li><li><strong><em>Determine a compliance <a href=\"/trac/trac-review-process-and-progress\">rating</a></em></strong>:&nbsp; the is a determination of compliance by the organization completing the review based on available evidence at a point in time (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Track status</em></strong>: enter the current status for identifying evidence for each requirement (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Define action items</em></strong>: identify steps needed to increase compliance (Optional, default setting = not public)</li><li><strong><em>Add notes: </em></strong>enter any notes that will be helpful to the process, e.g., assist in prioritizing actions or identify organizational changes that might affect the status. &nbsp;(Optional, default setting = not public)</li><li><strong><em>Share your results and experiences</em></strong>: every digital repository would benefit from a self-assessment process using the TRAC requirement as a frame, all organizations&nbsp; will benefit from shared experiences</li></ul><p>NOTE:&nbsp; The default setting is for the content to be public except for action items and notes, but organizations can change those settings locally. Identifying roles and responsibilities for requirements has proven to be an effective way for organizations to engage staff across the organization in completing a TRAC review.&nbsp; The compliance ratings and status tracking options allow an organization to manage a TRAC review like a project showing progress and meeting milestones. An organization can choose not to do optional steps and still effectively use this TRAC Review site.</p><h2>TRAC Review Site Content</h2><p>This TRAC Review site consists of:</p><ul><li><strong><em>Home</em></strong>: provides a brief introduction to the site, links to a page for each TRAC requirement displaying its current compliance rating and status, and a summary that reflects cumulative compliance ratings the three sections of TRAC</li><li><strong><em>Responsibilities</em></strong>: describes optional roles and responsibilities an organization can assign to individuals and units and links to each stakeholder group to review the status of its assigned requirements</li><li><strong><em>Requirements</em></strong>: provides all of the information in the CCSDS about each TRAC requirement and fields that can be edited by authenticated users to indicate roles, responsibilities, compliance rating, action items, and notes the organization can enter for each requirement</li></ul><h2>Development Milestones</h2><p><strong>2008&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> Version 1.0 was initiated and specified by Nancy McGovern using the 2007 TRAC requirements for internal use by the Inter-University Consortium for Political and Social Research, with the technical development completed by Matthew Richardson and Michael Iannaccone.</p><p><strong>2013&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> Version 2.0 was initiated and specified by Nancy McGovern using the 2012 version of the TRAC requirements for the Digital Preservation Management workshop series that is hosted by MIT Libraries implementation, with content management by Liz Francis and technical development by Matt Bernhardt.</p><p><strong>2013&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> The TRAC Review site files are available for download from <a href=\"http://www.artefactual.com/index.html\">Artefactual</a> Systems as a tarball that contains a complete and standalone Drupal instance.&nbsp;</p><p>This is version 2.0 of the TRAC Review site. It has been reviewed by a few organizations. There are no specific plans to extend or update the site.&nbsp; Organizations are welcome to use and extend the site and hopefully share their developments.</p><h2>Advice and Assistance</h2><p>The TRAC Review site is available open source and as is for organizations to use.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>If you have questions about implementing or using Drupal, you should be able to find local or online Drupal assistance.&nbsp;</li><li>If you have questions about completing a TRAC Review, one source of advice and information is the National Digital Stewardship Alliance (NDSA) <a href=\"http://www.digitalpreservation.gov/ndsa/working_groups/standards.html\">Standards</a> working group that is working on guidance for conducting a peer review audit.</li></ul>','','plain_text');
