equirement',0,113,246,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that data is not lost when either the media fail or the\r\nsupporting hardware can no longer be used to access the data.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,114,194,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the critical processes can be monitored to ensure that\r\nthey continue to meet the mandatory responsibilities and to ensure that any changes to those\r\nprocesses are examined and tested.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,114,247,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the critical processes can be monitored to ensure that\r\nthey continue to meet the mandatory responsibilities and to ensure that any changes to those\r\nprocesses are examined and tested.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,115,195,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository can specify not only the current\r\nprocesses, but the prior processes that were applied to the repository holdings.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,115,248,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that the repository can specify not only the current\r\nprocesses, but the prior processes that were applied to the repository holdings.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,116,196,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to protect the integrity of the repository’s critical processes such\r\nthat they continue in their ability to meet the repository’s mandatory requirements.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,116,249,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to protect the integrity of the repository’s critical processes such\r\nthat they continue in their ability to meet the repository’s mandatory requirements.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,117,197,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that multiple copies of a digital object remain identical,\r\nwithin a time established as acceptable by the repository, and that a copy can be used to\r\nreplace a corrupted copy of the object.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,117,250,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to ensure that multiple copies of a digital object remain identical,\r\nwithin a time established as acceptable by the repository, and that a copy can be used to\r\nreplace a corrupted copy of the object.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,119,316,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to preserve the information content entrusted to the repository by\r\nhanding it on to another custodian in the case that the repository ceases to operate.','',NULL),('node','trac_requirement',0,119,425,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to preserve the information content entrusted to the repository by handing it on to another custodian in the case that the repository ceases to operate.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,119,434,'und',0,'<p>This is necessary in order to preserve the information content entrusted to the repository by handing it on to another custodian in the case that the repository ceases to operate.</p>','','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,120,331,'und',0,'This is necessary in order to identify in writing the Content Information of the records for\r\nwhich it has taken preservation responsibility and the Information Properties it has\r\ncommitted to preserve for those records based on their Content Information.','',NULL),('node','page',0,121,429,'und',0,'<h2>Purpose and Scope</h2><p>This site is designed to assist any organization with responsibility for the long-term management of digital content to completing a TRAC Review as a means to demonstrate its alignment with prevailing digital curation and preservation standards and good practice.</p><p>The site supports both self-assessment and preparation for an external audit. There is an auditor role with a separate log-in that can see all of the content on the site and has exclusive editing rights to an audit comment field.&nbsp; Organization’s can incorporate the auditor role into their TRAC review process. One possible approach might be to freeze the content and effectively turning the site over to one or more auditors for a period of time then reviewing the results. The TRAC Review site is intentionally not prescriptive about how the site is used so any organization can use it.</p><h2>TRAC Requirements</h2><p>This TRAC Review site reflects the requirements as defined in the CCSDS Audit and Certification of Trustworthy Digital Repositories <a title=\"checklist\" href=\"http://public.ccsds.org/publications/archive/652x0m1.pdf\">checklist</a> that was approved as ISO 16363 in 2012. &nbsp;ISO 16363 is based on the Trustworthy Repository Audit and Certification (<a href=\"http://www.crl.edu/sites/default/files/attachments/pages/trac_0.pdf\">TRAC</a>): Criteria and Checklist that was developed by the RLG/NARA Task Force beginning in 2003 and released for public use in January 2007. The requirements pages reflect the 2012 version of the requirements with a link to the relevant 2007 version of the requirement. All of the information from the CCSDS document is included in this TRAC review site.</p><h2>Process</h2><p>This site incorporates an optional approach to roles and responsibilities that adopts the <a href=\"http://www.valuebasedmanagement.net/methods_raci.html\">RA(S)CI</a> project management roles as described on the Responsibilities page (see links for information about those aspects).&nbsp; The process envisioned in using this TRAC Review site includes completing the following steps for each requirement (noting optional steps):</p><ul><li><strong><em>Identify <a href=\"/trac/responsibilities\">roles</a></em></strong>: e.g., senior management, preservation, rights management&nbsp; (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Assign <a href=\"/trac/responsibilities\">responsibilities</a></em></strong>: e.g., responsible, accountable, support, consulted, informed (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Enter evidence</em></strong>: note who provided what evidence when using the examples from the CCSDS document as a guide to provide a cumulative record and to show progress (Required)</li><li><strong><em>Determine a compliance <a href=\"/trac/trac-review-process-and-progress\">rating</a></em></strong>:&nbsp; the is a determination of compliance by the organization completing the review based on available evidence at a point in time (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Track status</em></strong>: enter the current status for identifying evidence for each requirement (Optional)</li><li><strong><em>Define action items</em></strong>: identify steps needed to increase compliance (Optional, default setting = not public)</li><li><strong><em>Add notes: </em></strong>enter any notes that will be helpful to the process, e.g., assist in prioritizing actions or identify organizational changes that might affect the status. &nbsp;(Optional, default setting = not public)</li><li><strong><em>Share your results and experiences</em></strong>: every digital repository would benefit from a self-assessment process using the TRAC requirement as a frame, all organizations&nbsp; will benefit from shared experiences</li></ul><p>NOTE:&nbsp; The default setting is for the content to be public except for action items and notes, but organizations can change those settings locally. Identifying roles and responsibilities for requirements has proven to be an effective way for organizations to engage staff across the organization in completing a TRAC review.&nbsp; The compliance ratings and status tracking options allow an organization to manage a TRAC review like a project showing progress and meeting milestones. An organization can choose not to do optional steps and still effectively use this TRAC Review site.</p><h2>TRAC Review Site Content</h2><p>This TRAC Review site consists of:</p><ul><li><strong><em>Home</em></strong>: provides a brief introduction to the site, links to a page for each TRAC requirement displaying its current compliance rating and status, and a summary that reflects cumulative compliance ratings the three sections of TRAC</li><li><strong><em>Responsibilities</em></strong>: describes optional roles and responsibilities an organization can assign to individuals and units and links to each stakeholder group to review the status of its assigned requirements</li><li><strong><em>Requirements</em></strong>: provides all of the information in the CCSDS about each TRAC requirement and fields that can be edited by authenticated users to indicate roles, responsibilities, compliance rating, action items, and notes the organization can enter for each requirement</li></ul><h2>Development Milestones</h2><p><strong>2008&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> Version 1.0 was initiated and specified by Nancy McGovern using the 2007 TRAC requirements for internal use by the Inter-University Consortium for Political and Social Research, with the technical development completed by Matthew Richardson and Michael Iannaccone.</p><p><strong>2013&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> Version 2.0 was initiated and specified by Nancy McGovern using the 2012 version of the TRAC requirements for the Digital Preservation Management workshop series that is hosted by MIT Libraries implementation, with content management by Liz Francis and technical development by Matt Bernhardt.</p><p><strong>2013&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> The TRAC Review site files are available for download from <a href=\"http://www.artefactual.com/index.html\">Artefactual</a> Systems as a tarball that contains a complete and standalone Drupal instance.&nbsp;</p><p>This is version 2.0 of the TRAC Review site. It has been reviewed by a few organizations. There are no specific plans to extend or update the site.&nbsp; Organizations are welcome to use and extend the site and hopefully share their developments.</p><h2>Advice and Assistance</h2><p>The TRAC Review site is available open source and as is for organizations to use.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>If you have questions about implementing or using Drupal, you should be able to find local or online Drupal assistance.&nbsp;</li><li>If you have questions about completing a TRAC Review, one source of advice and information is the National Digital Stewardship Alliance (NDSA) <a href=\"http://www.digitalpreservation.gov/ndsa/working_groups/standards.html\">Standards</a> working group that is working on guidance for conducting a peer review audit.</li></ul>','','plain_text');
