....\" at: <a href=\"http://web.mit.edu/facts/mission.html\">http://web.mit.edu/facts/mission.html</a>&nbsp;(Added by Curation and Preservation Services, 6/5/2013)</li></ul>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,7,489,'und',0,'<ul><li>URL - DCP date</li></ul>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,7,490,'und',0,'<ul><li><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'; font-size: 11pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">One of the stated goals of the Minnesota Population Center is to “To produce and disseminate nationally and internationally recognized research and data products for population research.” (<a href=\"http://www.pop.umn.edu/sites/www.pop.umn.edu/files/By-laws_Oct%202010.pdf\">By-Laws</a>, October 2010)</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'; font-size: 11pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">The TerraPop project is described in the Project Execution Plan, particularly Section 2, Project Description (p. 2-4). In sum: The central goal of the project is to create a sustainable organization for the integration, preservation, and dissemination of global-scale data on the human population and the environment over a decades-long time frame. The project involves four key elements: (1) developing an archive, (2) creating new software and methods for data access and integration, (3) conducting education and outreach; and (4) designing a new organizational structure (TerraPop Project Execution Plan, 6-18-12).</span></li></ul>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,7,491,'und',0,'<ul><li>URL - DCP date</li></ul>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,31,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,32,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,33,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,34,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,35,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,41,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,359,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,424,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,8,432,'und',0,'<p>Here we list the evidence provided.</p>','plain_text'),('node','trac_requirement',0,19,439,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica calculates sha-256 checksums for each file and validates any that are provided with the transferred SIP content.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,19,492,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica calculates sha-256 checksums for each file and validates any that are provided with the transferred SIP content.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,26,440,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica micro-services are designed to recognize several submission types and validate their compliance within the system. These specifications allow for SIP parsing and processing via a series of micro-services. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Archivematica_1.0_Micro-services</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,27,441,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica uses FITS to extract any SIP metadata, registers the Archivematica user as PREMIS agent and allows for creator information to be included in the Dublin Core template form or as a csv as part of the transfer.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,28,444,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica micro-services are designed to recognize several submission types and validate their compliance within the system. Checksums, if provided with the transfer, are verified, and packages are checked for malware content.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,29,442,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica creates an AIP with the originals as well as, if the user specifies, preservation copies. The original structure of each transferred package is also retained in the AIP METS profile.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,30,443,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica communicates the success or failure of micro-services and provides individual task and job error reports so the user can drill down to what went wrong with the transfer if errors occur.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,32,445,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica creates a consistent and&nbsp; standardized AIP structure. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/AIP_structure</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,33,448,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica documentation is complete and freely available via their wiki. Code is available on GitHub. archivematica.org and https://github.com/artefactual/archivematica</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,34,449,'und',0,'<p>The AIP contains information about the final processed package content as well as what was in the original transferred package(s) so that any transformation is clear.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,35,451,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica assigns UUIDs to each AIP.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,37,463,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica manages PDI using PREMIS in METS xml as part of the AIP. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Metadata_elements</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,39,468,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica allows users to review the AIP prior to uploading it to storage.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,40,469,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica recommends regular fixity checking of the AIP storage.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,41,470,'und',0,'<p>During the ingest process, Archivematica logs micro-service actions and collects preservation (PREMIS) metadata about the creation of the AIP. Problems are recorded as errors and are reported on by the dashboard and in error reports (email and in the administrative tab of the dashboard). The AIP storage tab of the dashboard shows the location of the content object, its size and its UUID. Events are recorded at the time they occur. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Metadata_elements</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,42,471,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica preservation strategies are documented on the wiki via the format policy page. The format policsy registry stores default format policies as well as those submitted by repositories. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Format_policies</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,43,472,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica and the broader user community monitors the digital preservation and curation fields for emergent standards and best practices. The Format Policy Registry contains Archivematica\'s default format policies, which may change over time due to community developments. Additionally, the FPR can accommodate user specified format policies, which can then in turn be applied to local instances based on user need. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Format_policy_registry and fpr.archivematica.org</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,44,474,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica allows for manual application of preservation strategies (normalization, migration to access and preservation copies), the ability to add new tools, and the ability to add and/or change format policies via the format policy registry. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Administrator_manual_1.0#Format_Policy_Registry_.28FPR.29 , https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/UM_manual_normalization and fpr.archivematica.org</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,45,476,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica creates valid PREMIS metadata and stores it METS in the AIP.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,46,477,'und',0,'<p>AIPs are structured consistently, stored in a designated preservation repository and storage is managed via a Storage Service. AIP content is indexed using ElasticSearch. PREMIS and METS files in the AIP contain descriptive and structural metadata about the object(s) within. Additionally, the&nbsp; metadata contains format information such that the object is interpretable down to the bit-level. These components are packaged together with the AIP contents&nbsp; using the BagIt specification, and the METS file includes relationship and event links.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,46,478,'und',0,'<p>AIPs are structured consistently and packaged using the Library of Congress BagIt specification. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/AIP_structure</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,47,480,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica manages AIP storage via the AIP storage dashboard and the Storage Service. AIP location is recorded in the Archivematica database as well as linked via the content management system. Archivematica automatically captures events that occur throught the ingest process using PREMIS events to record registration, image capture, ingestion, fixity check, message digest calculation, identifier assignment, unpacking, quarantine/unquarantine, virus check, name cleanup, format identification, validation, normalization, and creation [of the AIP]. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/PREMIS_metadata:_events</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,48,483,'und',0,'<p>The AIP METS.xml file is indexed using ElasticSearch and searchable within the Archivematica dashboard. The DIP may include simple Dublin Core, PREMIS rights and other ingested metadata for sharing with the content management system.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,49,484,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica preserves any descriptive information supplied by the user at the time of ingest via its metadata import function. In the dashboard, the user may also add simple Dublin Core elements and PREMIS rights and restrictions&nbsp; information. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Metadata_import</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,50,485,'und',0,'<p>The Archivematica AIP contains any descriptive information provided upon ingest as well as PREMIS metadata. The descriptive information is shared with the content management system and can be augmented there, but should always link back to the AIP UUID. The AIP location is managed using the Storage Service and the Archivematica dashboard and database, which contain the UUID, the size and the location of the AIP.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,52,486,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica DIPs and AIPs are linked through use of a UUID. The AIP\'s METS.xml contains PREMIS metadata&nbsp; that records all the events that occur to the object(s) during ingest, as well as information about the original SIP(s) that made up the resulting AIP. The METS file is indexed via ElasticSearch and searchable via the Archivmatica dashboard.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,71,446,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica AIPs are assigned UUIDs and have a consistent internal structure. They are also tracked via the Archivematica storage service and database. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/AIP_structure</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,72,447,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica creates a consistent and&nbsp; standardized AIP structure. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/AIP_structure</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,74,452,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica assigns UUIDs to each AIP. Identifier assignment is captured as a PREMIS event and stored in the METS profile of each AIP.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,74,454,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica assigns UUIDs to each AIP. Identifier assignment is captured as a PREMIS event and stored in the METS profile of each AIP. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/PREMIS_metadata:_events</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,75,453,'und',0,'<p>The repository identifier is assigned by the repository.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,75,538,'und',0,'<p>The repository identifier is assigned by the repository.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,76,455,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica assigns UUIDs to each AIP and to each file in the transferred package contents and the final AIP contents.. The event of identifier assignment is captured as a PREMIS event. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Archivematica_1.0_Micro-services</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,79,456,'und',0,'<p>As of Archivematica 1.0, program=\"UUID\"; version=\"1.6.2\"</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,80,457,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica maintains an ElasticSearch index of AIPs and their METS profiles which links to the AIP storage location in the repository.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,81,458,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica uses open source tools and file extension to identify file types during initial package transfer. During ingest, the user has options to use several different tools for file identification. The Format Policy registry allows users to assign new tools for this purpose as they become available.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,82,459,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica provides default normalization for preservation and access copies that is based on a comprehensive review of formats and significant properties/characteristics. Users may choose to forego these defaults and replace them with their own based on their own analysis and/or do migration work using manual methods outside of the system. Users can also add new tools for normalization using the Format Policy Registry.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,82,460,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica provides default normalization for preservation and access copies that is based on a comprehensive review of formats and significant properties/characteristics. Users may choose to forego these defaults and replace them with their own based on their own analysis and/or do migration work using manual methods outside of the system. Users can also add new tools for normalization using the Format Policy Registry. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Significant_characteristics</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,83,461,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica default preservation and access formats are chosen so they are compliant with open and ubiquitous rendering viewers/tools. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Format_policies</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,84,462,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica default preservation and access formats are chosen so they are compliant with open and ubiquitous rendering viewers/tools.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,85,464,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica manages PDI using PREMIS in METS xml as part of the AIP. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Metadata_elements</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,86,465,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica manages PDI using PREMIS in METS xml as part of the AIP. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Metadata_elements</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,87,466,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica manages PDI using PREMIS in METS xml as part of the AIP. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Metadata_elements</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,89,467,'und',0,'<p>The PREMIS metadata gathered within the AIP and the metadata used to describe the DIP in the content management system can be used to evaluate the composition of the collections in the repository\'s content management system, so that objects at risk of not being usable, understandable, or accessible by the Designated Community can be identified and, if necessary, transformed.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,91,473,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica community members and Artefactual Systems, Inc., will track preservation strategies over time and update format policies via the format policy registry to ensure understandability and usability. https://www.archivematica.org/wiki/Administrator_manual_1.0#Format_Policy_Registry_.28FPR.29 and fpr.archivematica.org</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,92,475,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica keeps any extra representation information in PREMIS and in system logs. Users can update their local policies from the Format Policy Registry, which is to stay current with community best practices.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,93,479,'und',0,'<p>AIPs are structured consistently, stored in a designated preservation repository and storage is managed via a Storage Service. AIP content is indexed using ElasticSearch. PREMIS and METS files in the AIP contain descriptive and structural metadata about the object(s) within. Additionally, the&nbsp; metadata contains format information such that the object is interpretable down to the bit-level. These components are packaged together with the AIP contents&nbsp; using the BagIt specification, and the METS file includes relationship and event links.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,95,481,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica micro-services are documented on the archivematica.org wiki. Each micro-service is described in detail and preservation actions are registered as PREMIS metadata in the METS xml of the stored AIP. Archivematica logs and detailed error reports are also available. Once an AIP is stored in the preservation environment, it is not deleted as part of normal operations. A request must be sent to the storage administrator who must affirm the validity of the reason given for deletion prior to carrying out the deletion event. All deletion requests and results are logged in the Storage Service.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,95,521,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica micro-services are documented on the archivematica.org wiki. Each micro-service is described in detail and preservation actions are registered as PREMIS metadata in the METS xml of the stored AIP. Archivematica logs and detailed error reports are also available. Once an AIP is stored in the preservation environment, it is not deleted as part of normal operations. A request must be sent to the storage administrator who must affirm the validity of the reason given for deletion prior to carrying out the deletion event. All deletion requests and results are logged in the Storage Service.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,96,482,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica allows the user to review the AIP at time of storage, including the METS.xml file with the preservation and other metadata. Once stored, the AIP\'s location, UUID and size are recorded in the Archivematica dashboard, Storage Service and database.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,99,488,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica generates error reports for tasks in the dashboard as well as via email and in the administrative tab when DIP creation and upload fails for any reason.</p>','filtered_html'),('node','trac_requirement',0,109,487,'und',0,'<p>Archivematica AIPs have a UUID which is stored in both the Archivematica dashboard and database as well as in the Storage Service, which tracks the AIP location. Location is also linked in the dashboard Archival Storage tab along with size and name information.</p>','filtered_html');
